## PRODUCT SCOPE

### In Scope

- **Document Indexing:** Creating searchable collections from Jira, Confluence, and files
- **Semantic Search:** Vector-based similarity search with natural language queries
- **Collection Management:** Creating, updating, deleting, and inspecting collections
- **CLI Interface:** Command-line commands for all operations
- **MCP Server:** Model Context Protocol server for AI agent integration
- **Plugin Architecture:** Connector system for adding new data sources
- **Configuration Management:** Hierarchical config system with TOML, environment variables, and CLI overrides
- **Storage Modes:** Global (~/.indexed/) and local (./.indexed/) storage options
- **Multi-format Support:** PDF, DOCX, PPTX, Markdown, plain text, and more

### Out of Scope

- **Cloud Hosting:** Indexed is a local application, not a cloud service
- **User Authentication:** Single-user local application, no built-in auth
- **Web UI:** CLI and MCP interfaces only (no web dashboard)
- **Real-time Sync:** One-way indexing with manual refresh
- **Encryption:** Relies on filesystem permissions (user's responsibility)
- **Advanced Analytics:** No usage tracking or analytics features
- **Custom Embedding Models:** Uses pre-trained sentence-transformers models only
- **Fine-tuning:** Models cannot be fine-tuned on user data

