## NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

### Privacy & Security
- MUST process all documents locally without any external API calls for indexing
- MUST NOT send document content to any third-party service (including embedding providers)
- MUST support offline operation after initial setup
- MUST use local embedding models only (sentence-transformers)
- MUST provide option to store sensitive credentials in .env files

### Reliability & Maintainability
- MUST maintain clear separation of concerns across CLI, Service, and Engine layers
- MUST use protocol-based design enabling plugin architecture
- MUST provide comprehensive error messages with actionable guidance
- MUST implement graceful degradation (skip problematic documents, continue indexing)
- MUST maintain backward compatibility with existing collections

### Extensibility
- MUST support easy addition of new data source connectors via plugin architecture
- MUST not require core code modifications to add new connectors
- MUST use configuration-driven behavior instead of hardcoded logic
- MUST support both library usage and CLI usage without duplication

### Usability
- MUST provide clear, intuitive CLI commands with consistent structure
- MUST show progress indicators for long-running operations
- MUST provide helpful error messages when operations fail
- MUST support JSON output for scripting and automation
- MUST implement smart defaults to minimize required configuration

