## ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA

The product MUST meet these criteria to be considered complete:

### Functional Criteria
- Semantic search returns relevant results from indexed documents
- Collections can be created, updated, and deleted without errors
- CLI commands execute reliably with clear output
- MCP server successfully connects to Claude, Cursor, and Cline
- Multiple connector types work without core code modifications

### Non-Functional Criteria
- Search responses complete in < 1 second for typical collections
- All data remains local with zero external data transmission
- Application functions offline after initial setup
- Configuration system supports TOML, environment variables, and CLI overrides
- Plugin architecture enables community connector contributions

### Quality Criteria
- Code maintains high test coverage (target: > 85%)
- All major components have clear documentation
- Error messages provide actionable guidance
- Design patterns are consistently applied across modules
- Architecture remains maintainable as codebase grows

